either stasis or flux in ordinary macroscopic phenomena. If we watch the
water flow from a tap we see flux, if we watch the standing pattern of the
surface of the falling water we see stasis. Changes in that stasis cannot
occur faster than the flux which carry them, but previous interaction
retains connection.

