modified by the flux of b and vice versa. Given the knowledge of
constraints we can assert superposed stases and do calculations without
needing b resolved, so long as we accept that we don't know b and that the
underlying connections in everything can determine it, including our own
interactions and choices. That it works is interesting, but that doesn't
justify live-dead cats. Any model that leaves states like those is in need
